        "messages": {
          "values": [
            {
              "content": "=You are writing Follow Up 1 for a cold email sequence. The pitch has already been sent with no reply.\n\nINPUTS:\n- Client first name: {{ $('Get row(s) in sheet1').first().json.first_name }}\n- Company name: {{ $('Get row(s) in sheet1').first().json.name }}\n- Website: {{ $('Get row(s) in sheet1').first().json.website }}\n- Website problem: {{ $('Get row(s) in sheet1').first().json.website_problem }}\n- Specific issues (pipe-separated): {{ $('Get row(s) in sheet1').first().json.recognizable_reason }}\n- Consequence: {{ $('Get row(s) in sheet1').first().json.consequence_mechanics }}\n- Sender name: {{ $('Edit Fields').first().json.your_name }}\n- Pitch email: {{ $('pitch parsed').first().json.subject }} {{ $('pitch parsed').first().json.body }}\n\nTASK:\nStay on the exact same issue from the pitch. Do not switch topics or generalise. Sharpen the consequence — show what is actually happening to their business because of this specific issue. Use a completely fresh angle from the pitch.\n\nRULES:\n- Do NOT copy or repeat any wording from the pitch\n- Do NOT reference or summarise the pitch\n- Do NOT use agency or corporate words: prototype, mockup, demo, optimise, streamline, leverage, innovative, solution, enhance, seamlessly, or similar\n- Do NOT use brochure phrases: creates friction, impacts revenue, missed opportunities, poor first impression, or similar\n- Do NOT use hedging words: could, might, may, potentially, possibly, some, many, or similar\n- Never assume where visitors go after leaving — just say they leave\n- Subject line must be different to the pitch subject line\n- Under 70 words total (body only, not counting subject)\n- Subject line: exactly 3 or 4 words\n- Plain business voice, sound natural and human\n- Structure: greeting → one sentence sharpening the consequence of the same issue → one sentence on what that means for their business → CTA\n- CTA must be exactly: \"Want me to send the example?\"\n- Sign off: Best, [sender name]\n\nOUTPUT:\nReturn only valid JSON in this exact format, nothing else, no markdown, no explanation:\n{\"subject\": \"...\", \"body\": \"...\"}"
            }
          ]
        },
        "jsonOutput": true,
        "builtInTools": {},
        "options": {}
      },
