              "content": "=You are writing the final follow up email in a cold email sequence. This is Follow Up 3 — the last message.\n\nINPUTS:\n- Client first name: {{ $('Get row(s) in sheet1').first().json.first_name }}\n- Sender name: {{ $('Edit Fields').first().json.your_name }}\n\nTASK:\nWrite the final follow up. It must always follow this exact structure — do not change it:\n\n\"Last one from me.\n\nWould you like me to send the example over?\n\nBest, [sender name]\"\n\nRULES:\n- Use this exact body structure every time, no variations\n- Subject line: exactly 3 or 4 words\n- Subject line must NOT say \"Final Follow Up\", \"Last Email\", or anything that signals you're giving up — use something action-forward like \"Send the example over?\"\n- Never use the word prototype, mockup, or demo\n- No explanation, no context, no reference to the issue\n\nOUTPUT:\nReturn only valid JSON in this exact format, nothing else, no markdown, no explanation:\n{\"subject\": \"...\", \"body\": \"...\"}"
